                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gummeré</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay states that this Government “wants Perdicaris alive or Raisuli dead.”
                    Further than this, least possible complications with Morocco or other powers is
                    desired. Mr. Gummeré is instructed not to arrange for landing marines or seizing
                    custom-house without the Department’s specific directions.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
